Date: 6 July 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Office International des Epizooties (OIE), Disease Information 21
June 2002 [edited] <http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_64.HTM#Sec0>

Foot and mouth disease in Republic of Korea
-------------------------------------------
(Follow-up report No. 4: see also: 21 and 7 June 2002, 31 and 10 May 2002,
and 21 September 2001)
Information received on 28 June 2002 from Dr Hee-Woo Lee, Director, Animal
Health Division, Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry (MAF), Seoul:
Previous report period ended 14 June 2002 (see Disease Information, 15
[25], 100, dated 21 June 2002). End of this report period: 28 June 2002.
One new outbreak: in the province: Kyonggi, district: Anseong, locality:
Iljuk. Species code: sui. Six cases and 2 deaths among 3575 susceptible
animals, 3753 animals destroyed
Clinical inspection and serological and virological testing at the National
Veterinary Research and Quarantine Service, Anyang, Kyonggi province
confirmed the diagnosis.
Causal agent: foot and mouth disease virus serotype O.
The affected holding is about 700 m away from the last affected pig
holding. The source of agent/origin of infection and mode of spread are
under investigation.
Control measures during reporting period:
- movement control, cleaning, and disinfection were maintained;
- all the pigs and cattle in the affected farm were destroyed on 24 June 2002;
- pre-emptive slaughter of 2684 pigs and 63 dairy cattle from 3 livestock
farms within a 500 m radius of the infected farm was carried out;
- in addition, pre-emptive slaughter will be extended to all domestic pigs
within a 3 km radius;
- screening;
- vaccination remains prohibited;
- zoning.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[One must read this message carefully. The new outbreak is only 700 meters
away from the previous outbreak farm as reported in Foot & mouth disease -
S. Korea: OIE (03) 20020624.4590. The outbreak still smolders but appears
to be contained - Mod.PC]
